@page "/"

<PageTitle>Welcome — Simply Job Application</PageTitle>

<div class="welcome-hero py-5 text-center mb-5">
    <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold mb-2">Simply Job Application</h1>
    <p class="lead text-muted mx-auto" style="max-width:560px">
        AI-powered resume tailoring and cover letter generation — entirely in your browser,
        with no data sent to any server except the AI model of your choice.
    </p>
    <div class="d-flex justify-content-center gap-3 mt-4">
        <a href="/evaluate" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg px-4">Get Started</a>
        <a href="/settings" class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-lg px-4">Configure API Key</a>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row g-4 mb-5">
    <div class="col-12">
        <h5 class="text-uppercase text-muted fw-semibold small mb-3 letter-spacing-1">What it does</h5>
    </div>

    <div class="col-12 col-md-4">
        <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
            <div class="card-body">
                <div class="welcome-step-num mb-3">1</div>
                <h6 class="fw-bold mb-2">Evaluate the Match</h6>
                <p class="text-muted small mb-0">
                    Paste a job description and upload your resume. The AI scores how well you
                    match the role, identifies your strongest qualifications, and flags any gaps
                    against the stated requirements.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-12 col-md-4">
        <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
            <div class="card-body">
                <div class="welcome-step-num mb-3">2</div>
                <h6 class="fw-bold mb-2">Add Missing Keywords</h6>
                <p class="text-muted small mb-0">
                    Review AI-suggested keywords that appear in the job description but not in
                    your resume. Check the ones you genuinely have experience with, or type your
                    own. Re-run the evaluation to see how the score changes.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-12 col-md-4">
        <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
            <div class="card-body">
                <div class="welcome-step-num mb-3">3</div>
                <h6 class="fw-bold mb-2">Generate Tailored Materials</h6>
                <p class="text-muted small mb-0">
                    With one click, get a tailored resume DOCX, a two-paragraph cover letter,
                    and a concise "why apply" summary — all optimised for ATS and ready to
                    download.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row g-4 mb-5">
    <div class="col-12">
        <h5 class="text-uppercase text-muted fw-semibold small mb-3">Who it's for</h5>
    </div>
    <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
        <ul class="list-unstyled d-flex flex-column gap-2 mb-0">
            <li class="d-flex gap-2">
                <span class="text-success fw-bold">✓</span>
                <span class="text-muted small">Job seekers who apply to multiple roles and need
                    position-specific resumes without rewriting from scratch each time.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="d-flex gap-2">
                <span class="text-success fw-bold">✓</span>
                <span class="text-muted small">Professionals returning to the market who want
                    to quickly gauge how well their experience aligns with modern job postings.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="d-flex gap-2">
                <span class="text-success fw-bold">✓</span>
                <span class="text-muted small">Anyone who wants to maximise ATS pass-through
                    without guessing which keywords matter for a specific role.</span>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
        <ul class="list-unstyled d-flex flex-column gap-2 mb-0">
            <li class="d-flex gap-2">
                <span class="text-success fw-bold">✓</span>
                <span class="text-muted small">Works across professions — the AI adapts its
                    evaluation criteria and terminology to whatever role you are applying for.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="d-flex gap-2">
                <span class="text-success fw-bold">✓</span>
                <span class="text-muted small">Privacy-conscious users who want AI assistance
                    without uploading their resume to a third-party service.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="d-flex gap-2">
                <span class="text-success fw-bold">✓</span>
                <span class="text-muted small">Users who maintain a files library of resumes
                    and want to quickly pick the right base document for each application.</span>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row g-4 mb-5">
    <div class="col-12">
        <h5 class="text-uppercase text-muted fw-semibold small mb-3">How to get started</h5>
    </div>
    <div class="col-12 col-md-8 col-lg-6">
        <ol class="d-flex flex-column gap-3 ps-0" style="list-style:none;counter-reset:steps">
            <li class="d-flex gap-3 align-items-start welcome-how-step">
                <span class="welcome-step-num flex-shrink-0">1</span>
                <span class="text-muted small">
                    <strong class="text-body">Get an API key.</strong>
                    Simply Job Application uses the OpenAI API.
                    Create a key at <strong>platform.openai.com</strong> and paste it into
                    <a href="/settings">Settings</a>.
                    Your key is stored only in your browser's local storage.
                </span>
            </li>
            <li class="d-flex gap-3 align-items-start welcome-how-step">
                <span class="welcome-step-num flex-shrink-0">2</span>
                <span class="text-muted small">
                    <strong class="text-body">Upload your resume.</strong>
                    On the <a href="/evaluate">Evaluate &amp; Generate</a> screen, upload a DOCX
                    file. The document is parsed locally — hyperlinks and formatting are
                    preserved for the round-trip back to DOCX.
                </span>
            </li>
            <li class="d-flex gap-3 align-items-start welcome-how-step">
                <span class="welcome-step-num flex-shrink-0">3</span>
                <span class="text-muted small">
                    <strong class="text-body">Paste the job description</strong> and click
                    <strong>Evaluate</strong>. Review the match score, strengths, gaps, and
                    suggested keywords. Select any keywords you are comfortable claiming and
                    optionally re-evaluate.
                </span>
            </li>
            <li class="d-flex gap-3 align-items-start welcome-how-step">
                <span class="welcome-step-num flex-shrink-0">4</span>
                <span class="text-muted small">
                    <strong class="text-body">Click Generate</strong> to produce your tailored
                    resume, cover letter, and why-apply summary. Download the DOCX files and
                    submit your application.
                </span>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="card border-0 bg-light mb-5">
    <div class="card-body py-4">
        <h6 class="fw-bold mb-2">🔒 Your data stays in your browser</h6>
        <p class="text-muted small mb-0">
            Resumes, job descriptions, evaluation results, and generated materials are stored
            exclusively in your browser's IndexedDB. Nothing is sent to any server operated by
            this application. The only external calls are to the OpenAI API using your own key,
            subject to OpenAI's data handling policies.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="text-center py-3 mb-2">
    <a href="/evaluate" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg px-5">Start Matching</a>
</div>

<style>
    .welcome-step-num {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        width: 2rem;
        height: 2rem;
        border-radius: 50%;
        background: #0d6efd;
        color: #fff;
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        flex-shrink: 0;
    }
</style>
